Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.57,0:00:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resume the Numbers Hunt!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.98,0:00:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo Yuma has a very strange pendant...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.10,0:00:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see it coming at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.51,0:00:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the Numbers Hunter would attack me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.07,0:00:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to protect Emperor's Key, Shark's soul was absorbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end the Emperor's Key was stolen anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.45,0:00:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention, Astral is still inside Emperor's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.56,0:00:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait, Astral, I'm coming to save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.41,0:00:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark! Shark! Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a hold of yourself Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.26,0:00:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are the results?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.54,0:00:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir, I'm analyzing it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.97,0:01:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito-{\i1}sama{\i0}, why are you so obsessed with this pendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.14,0:01:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know the truth of this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.34,0:01:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Faker chose not to tell me everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.52,0:01:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I shall find out myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito-{\i1}sama{\i0}, don't tell me that, you're trying to outsmart Dr. Faker-{\i1}sama{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.03,0:01:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just shut up and focus on your analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.92,0:01:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctors said there's no abnormality in his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.13,0:01:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, why is he still in this coma?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.79,0:01:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarise then, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.95,0:01:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...lost his consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.60,0:01:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.28,0:01:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark's soul was absorbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.60,0:01:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His soul was absorbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.56,0:01:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's so, Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, what's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.56,0:01:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you lose a duel to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.88,0:02:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Kaito-guy will seize the Numbers card along with the victim's soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.62,0:02:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now he has my Emperor's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.06,0:02:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral is still inside there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.05,0:02:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.33,0:02:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. There is a unique space inside Emperor's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.03,0:02:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always stays in that place if he's not with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.68,0:02:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In conclusion, Shark's soul and Astral who is inside Emperor's Key, are all in Kaito's hands now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.24,0:02:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's find Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how do we find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since he took that key, that must mean he's using it for research purposes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.49,0:02:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo summarise, he's trying to analyze it using a computer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.09,0:02:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, maybe we can find Emperor's Key after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.21,0:02:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.10,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable! There is another gravitational field inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.41,0:02:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gravitational field? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.14,0:03:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the interior of this pendant is connected with a Different Dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... it's the Astral world?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.76,0:03:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you open an entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.46,0:03:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spread the Computer Virus?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.77,0:03:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no other way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.07,0:03:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy who stole the Emperor's Key from Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, should be researching it with a computer right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we just need to hack into it successfully and find that data...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be a piece of cake considering your computer skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.74,0:03:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.85,0:03:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, Shark and Astral will never come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.59,0:03:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}, this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}, can't you help us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}, if you don't, then I will tell everyone that you're the one who spread the Bugman Virus!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.34,0:03:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, {\i1}Sensei{\i0},... you caused a heck of a lot chaos in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.93,0:03:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.50,0:04:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.11,0:04:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.44,0:04:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.98,0:04:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.66,0:04:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... Kotori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.29,0:04:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After finding the whereabouts of Kaito, you'll go after him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, ...and you'll duel him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.26,0:04:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotori...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.52,0:04:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand... that you want to save Astral and Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.64,0:04:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.27,0:04:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry - it's gonna be alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.99,0:04:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely won't lose to that Kaito-guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.70,0:04:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.98,0:04:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, class rep, is it really OK to spread the computer virus around?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.01,0:04:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! Although it's a virus, it's not a spam program.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.16,0:04:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This program can find all the data about Emperor's Key throughout the network!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.36,0:04:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By using the virus made by {\i1}Sensei{\i0}, we will definitely find Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s Emperor's key!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.26,0:05:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does {\i1}Sensei{\i0}'s virus take the shape of Bugman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.91,0:05:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.48,0:05:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it have any connection with the previous bugman incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.01,0:05:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely that can't be related to you, right {\i1}Sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Alright, the modification of the virus is done, go, BUGMAN!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Bugman!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.73,0:05:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.87,0:05:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they're all ingredients to color each day. \NDon't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.97,0:05:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth is, I was lonely. Until I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.45,0:06:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lied to myself that being alone was easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.23,0:06:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My favorite books and hobbies,\N they don't seem to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were the only one to nod in agreement with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.84,0:06:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness and sadness and anger and\N Do and Re and Mi and Fa and So and La and Ti and Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It doesn't work unless they're different,\N the harmony and the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.38,0:06:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one is exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.68,0:06:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because that's the reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.72,0:06:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the sounds are dissonant from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.15,0:06:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}don't give up on the strength that will get you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.39,0:06:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we reach the edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.46,0:06:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the view we see will be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.44,0:06:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're all ingredients to color each day.\N Don't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.54,0:06:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.61,0:06:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.23,0:07:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no response.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(390,473)}The fated Duel, Kaito vs Astral
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(217,409)}Numbers 22:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like material from Earth can't create any reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.41,0:07:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then try 'Barrier Light'.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.18,0:07:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use 'Barrier Light'.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we obtained that from the Balian World.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.78,0:07:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect no less from Kaito-sama! I never even thought of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.30,0:07:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the important 'Barrier Light' is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.65,0:07:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Without that energy source I can't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.46,0:07:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfectly fine to just use a little. Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... why... Understood...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.02,0:08:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My important, most important energy, allow me to give up a chunk of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.54,0:08:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use the barrier light close to the Emperor's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.82,0:08:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the pendent created a resonance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.37,0:08:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Currently the interior mass is increasing,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.29,0:08:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also changes have occurred in gravitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.01,0:08:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gate has opened...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.94,0:08:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the entrance to the Astral world?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.15,0:08:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.86,0:08:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this space?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.39,0:09:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where... where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.94,0:09:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally! A response!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.96,0:09:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to be the Warehouse in the 4th Terminal managed by Heartland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Emperor's Key is over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.16,0:09:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.80,0:09:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.85,0:09:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the messenger from the Astral world?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito, so it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.18,0:09:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.88,0:09:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fought with you once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.03,0:09:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:10:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so the origin of the Numbers attached itself to Yuma Tsukumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.79,0:10:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you take the Emperor's Key from Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this thing is called the Emperor's Key.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you trying to find the Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who should be asking that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.87,0:10:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers are... the pieces of my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.82,0:10:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Memory you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, that is why I am collecting the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.29,0:10:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you also doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.30,0:10:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To learn about the Astral world and the Numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.40,0:10:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to learn the secrets of the Balian World.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.30,0:10:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balian...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall recover all the Numbers and find the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.87,0:10:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hand over all of your Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.08,0:10:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So are we betting on each others Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.93,0:10:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destiny has opened the gate. Now, duel me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.75,0:10:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.24,0:10:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel Mode, Photon Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let the hunt for all of your Numbers begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaito... so the time for our battle has finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.98,0:11:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No more running or hiding...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.80,0:11:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.82,0:11:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,DUEL!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.10,0:11:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.94,0:11:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me Astral is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I play a Monster in face-down defense position!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.71,0:11:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I set one card and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:11:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The card I set is Gogogo Golem,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.67,0:12:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When it is in defense position, once per turn it cannot be destroyed by battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the other card I set is the trap card Battle Break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.12,0:12:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With this card, when my opponent's monster declares an attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.07,0:12:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That monster will be destroyed and the Battle Phase will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.24,0:12:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, how will you deal with this, Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.67,0:12:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.91,0:12:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First I will seal off your set card!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.79,0:12:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Reverse Buster!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.26,0:12:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Reverse Buster battles, it can seal the opponent's Magic and Trap cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.73,0:12:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Reverse Buster, attack the Monster in face-down defense position!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:12:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it'd be Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Reverse Buster!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.02,0:13:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Reverse Buster battles a Monster in face-down defense position,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.23,0:13:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it can destroy that monster without applying Damage Calculation!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The timing of activation for Gogogo Golem's destruction-evading ability only applies during battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It cannot use its immunity against the destruction by card effects!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.22,0:13:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, when Reverse Buster destroys a Monster in face-down defense position through this effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.44,0:13:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its attack points increase by 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.69,0:13:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An attack power of 2000!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.97,0:13:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The conditions for Kaito to summon his Ace Monster Galaxy-Eyes are,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.87,0:13:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to release 2 Monsters with 2000 or more attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.37,0:13:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this monster a preparation to summon Galaxy-Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tch... anyway, if you think you can destroy my defense with a single Monster, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.74,0:13:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card, and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.25,0:13:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Kaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.25,0:14:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Dueling skills have always exceeded my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.44,0:14:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such an honor, but you won't lower my guard with flattery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.54,0:14:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the strongest duelist I know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.11,0:14:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Duel is filled with your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.19,0:14:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What made you that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... but can you really afford to observe me like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.83,0:14:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just say that I'm shouldering something different than what you guys normally do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.50,0:14:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.29,0:14:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your collecting of Numbers is related to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.92,0:14:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of telling you, someone who is about to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... what a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.20,0:14:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fascinated by you, you seem similar to Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.88,0:14:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.97,0:14:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, ever since I was attached to Yuma,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.37,0:14:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been able to feel his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.81,0:14:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deep inside Yuma's heart, there is the pain of losing his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.02,0:14:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And within that pain, there is determination to believe in his parents' words.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.36,0:15:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying... I'm the same as him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop joking around! I've never had parents to begin with, I only have Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.71,0:15:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking nonsense, let's resume the duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.30,0:15:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Gogogo Giant!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card is successfully summoned ,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.46,0:15:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can special summon Gogogo Golem from my graveyard in defense position!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.46,0:15:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when this effect is used, Gogogo Giant is switched to defense position!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now there are 2 Level 4 monsters on this guy's field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So here it comes, Aspiring Emperor Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.90,0:15:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1} Kaito's set card is the main problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:15:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is that card a trap to counter my Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.77,0:16:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Continuous Magic card from my hand, Double Defender!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.06,0:16:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When there are 2 monsters in face-up defense position, this card allows me to 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.85,0:16:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,once per turn, negate one attack from my opponent's monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.24,0:16:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card, and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.07,0:16:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were going to summon your ace Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.21,0:16:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you summoned Hope, Gogogo Giant and Gogogo Golem which are in defense position would disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.88,0:16:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you have Hope's ability, the number of total defenses will decrease.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.84,0:16:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those 2 set cards are to deal with my attacks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.50,0:16:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you worrying about my set card? \N Or are you simply afraid of Galaxy Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.13,0:16:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.09,0:16:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the magic card Photon Hurricane!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card returns the Magic and Trap cards on my opponent's field to their hand, up the number of cards in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now all of your set cards are back in your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.54,0:17:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.85,0:17:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, the set card you were afraid of...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... was just a Magic card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.74,0:17:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, there was no card to stop your attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had attacked last turn, now the situation would be much different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I release Reverse Buster to advance summon Photon Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Photon Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Howling Blow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.82,0:17:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card is summoned successfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.31,0:17:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The opponent must shuffle their hand into their deck, and draw the same number of cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.95,0:17:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, draw your new cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.49,0:18:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now all of your strategies go back to zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.95,0:18:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bit disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.08,0:18:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All your strategies have been all about defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bit too afraid, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.80,0:18:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open - open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open... open up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.61,0:18:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, the deck again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral is fighting. Astral is facing grave danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.67,0:18:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No clue, I just know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.78,0:18:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's fighting right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral? With whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.10,0:18:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the Numbers Hunter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn! Open, open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.95,0:18:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Equip Magic card Photon Spear and equip it to Photon Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.84,0:19:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the monster equipped with photon Spear attacks a monster in defense position,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.97,0:19:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If its ATK exceeds that monster's DEF, it inflicts the difference as battle damage to my opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Leo, attack Gogogo Giant!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silver Fang!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.28,0:19:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was I afraid of him without realizing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't win against Kaito this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.59,0:19:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I forgot my... most important lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its no use...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.97,0:19:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.36,0:19:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We came this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.07,0:19:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end... I couldn't save Astral and Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.87,0:20:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.67,0:20:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.66,0:20:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a hold of yourself! You can't be the first to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.61,0:20:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotori...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.58,0:20:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That... that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.91,0:20:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may be the only one who can save Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.51,0:20:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.57,0:20:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open! OPEN!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.02,0:20:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open! Open!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.78,0:20:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gate opened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.89,0:21:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just implanted a virus into the security system there. \NHurry up and infiltrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.80,0:21:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's awesome, Ukyo-{\i1}Sensei{\i0}! Let's go, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.45,0:21:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aaaa... Kaito-{\i1}sama{\i0}, Kaito-{\i1}sama{\i0}, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.48,0:21:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, if you are fine, please do reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.83,0:21:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OH! EEH? What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.63,0:21:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something big, Something big...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.18,0:21:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha- what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.71,0:21:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Invaders detected at area 3! Invaders detected...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.61,0:21:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are those guys? Wha... what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.35,0:21:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I try anything reckless now, he will turn me into scraps!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.41,0:21:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.52,0:21:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I suggest you give up this duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.17,0:22:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you to win against me, your heart needs to be stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.26,0:22:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I won't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.47,0:22:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed my former self would have given up already,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I won't give up now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.35,0:22:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to my most important friend, I have learned to {\i1}bring it to 'em{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.15,0:22:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did everyone already vote?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.75,0:22:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal popularity contest for Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.07,0:22:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which Numbers will be our first?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.06,0:22:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today's test is hard. I can't divide myself from pleasure and temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.13,0:22:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanna watch TV when I get home.\N The recent anime are fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.99,0:23:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In any case, this test is hard. \NLanguage, Math and English are especially bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.49,0:23:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm only average at science and social studies.\N The only thing I'm good at is P.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.67,0:23:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Wait up, Baby!) For who's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.37,0:23:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Is that, Baby!) ...am I remembering...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.81,0:23:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Just hold on, Baby!) ...the answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.37,0:23:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(What are we!? Baby!) ...they wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.04,0:23:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I write the correct answer on this paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in one year, in ten years, will anything change?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.52,0:23:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world I drew in the corner of my dreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.62,0:23:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}one day I will race through the open sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.40,0:23:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one can blame this heart of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.27,0:23:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing is really correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.72,0:23:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's ZeXal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.98,0:23:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The miraculous force which can save my world...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.12,0:23:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to get it! No matter at what price!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.35,0:24:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal! The soul Xyz Summon! ZeXal!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.75,0:24:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the second Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal popularity contest!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.18,0:24:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's Summon the six remaining ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.45,0:24:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 10: Illumiknight!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.31,0:24:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 20: Gig-Anto Brilli-Ant!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.55,0:24:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 12: Armored Ninja - Crimson Shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.97,0:24:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 16: Ruler of Color - Shock Ruler!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 11: Big Eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.48,0:24:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos No. 39: Utopia Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.51,0:24:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On our home webpage from TV-Tokyo you can tell us which is your favourite!
